In a [[Brillouin zone]], the '''constant-energy surface''' represents the [[locus (mathematics)|loci]] of all the <math>\vec{k}</math>-points (that is, all the [[crystal momentum]]  values) that have the same energy. [[Fermi surface]] is a special constant-energy surface that separates the unfilled orbitals from the filled ones at zero kelvin.

