'''Dryrock''' is the term used for processed [[phosphate]] [[rock (geology)|rock]], used in the production of agricultural [[fertilizer]]. Dryrock requires protection from the weather, and so is always shipped by [[Rail transport|rail]] using [[covered hopper]] and [[Gondola (rail)|gondola]] cars.

