'''Global Centre for Nuclear Energy Partnership''' is World's first nuclear energy partnership centre at [[Kheri Jasaur]] village of [[Bahadurgarh]] teshil in [[Jhajjar district]] of [[Haryana]] state in [[India]]. This center facilitates deliberation and discussions of international experts on various issues including innovation in nuclear reactors and the nuclear fuel cycle, development of proliferation-resistant reactors, security technologies and the effects of radiation exposure.<ref name="World's first nuclear energy partnership centre in state">{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-12-04/gurgaon/28266288_1_nuclear-security-reactors-nuclear-fuel-cycle|title=World's first nuclear energy partnership centre in state |date=December 4, 2010|work=TNN|publisher=Times of India|accessdate=28 December 2010|location=GURGAON}}</ref><ref name="France, Russia to assist India to set up global centre for nuclear energy">{{cite news|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/india/report_france-russia-to-assist-india-to-set-up-global-centre-for-nuclear-energy_1476182|title=France, Russia to assist India to set up global centre for nuclear energy|date=December 3, 2010|work=PTI|publisher=DNA|accessdate=28 December 2010|location=Chandigarh}}</ref><ref name="India warns of A.Q. Khan network, unveils global nuclear centre">{{cite news|url=http://www.sify.com/news/india-warns-of-a-q-khan-network-unveils-global-nuclear-centre-news-international-kenwkcgafje.html|title=India warns of A.Q. Khan network, unveils global nuclear centre|date=April 13, 2010 |publisher=Sifi news|accessdate=28 December 2010}}</ref><ref name="India to set up centre for N-energy applications">{{cite news|url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics/nation/India-to-set-up-centre-for-N-energy-applications/articleshow/5799258.cms|title=India to set up centre for N-energy applications|date=April 14, 2010|work=ET BUREAU|publisher=Economic Times|accessdate=28 December 2010|location=New Delhi}}</re