The '''lithospheric mantle''' is the uppermost solid part of [[mantle (geology)|mantle]].

the lithospheric mantle is subdvided into the [[subcontinental lithospheric mantle]] associated with the [[continental lithosphere]]<ref>{{Cite journal|jstor=3558903|title=The Continental Lithospheric Mantle: Characteristics and Significance as a mantle Reservoir|journal=Chemical reservoirs and convection in the Earth's mantle. Papers of a Discussion Meeting organized and edited by J. H. Davies|volume=360|issue=1800|pages=2383|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=|bibcode=2002RSPTA.360.2383P|author1=Pearson|first1=D. G.|last2=Nowell|first2=G. M.|year=2002|doi=10.1098/rsta.2002.1074}}</ref> and [[oceanic lithospheric mantle]], associated with the [[oceanic lithosphere]].<ref>[http://jgs.lyellcollection.org/content/168/4/995.abstract "Oceanic lithospheric mantle beneath the continental crust of the Chinese Altai"]</ref>

